ould be a corresponding negative impact on the company delays or inability in securing adequate supplies of refrigerants at peak demand periods lack of refrigerant demand increased expenses declining refrigerant prices and a loss of a principal customer could result in significant losses there can be no assurance that the foregoing factors will not occur and result in a material adverse effect on the companys financial position and significant losses the company believes that to a lesser extent there is a similar seasonal element to refrigerantsider service revenues as refrigerant sales the company is continuing to assess its refrigerantsider service revenues seasonal trend recent accounting pronouncements in january  the fasb issued accounting standards update asu no  intangiblesgoodwill and other topic  simplifying the test for goodwill impairment asu  which simplifies the accounting for goodwill impairment by eliminating step  of the current goodwill impairment test which requires a hypothetical purchase price allocation to measure goodwill impairment under the new standard a company will record an impairment charge based on the excess of a reporting units carrying amount over its fair value asu  does not change the guidance on completing step  of the goodwill impairment test and still allows a company to perform the optional qualitative goodwill impairment assessment before determining whether to proceed to step  the standard is effective for annual and interim goodwill impairment tests in fiscal years beginning after december   with early adoption permitted for any impairment test performed on testing dates after january   the company adopted this standard on january   and will apply its guidance on future impairment assessments in august  the fasb issued asu no  classification of certain cash receipts and cash payments this asu addresses eight specific cash flow issues with the objective of eliminating the existing diversity in practice the    may   c  cyberne