on can ensure that all reclaimed refrigerant meets or exceeds ari requirements and eliminates any quality concerns with the use of reclaimed refrigerant this enables reclaimed refrigerant to be reused and has reduced the impact of new refrigerant production on the environment our buyback and reclamation of refrigerants enables hudson to continue to supply the hvac and refrigeration industries with numerous refrigerants that are no longer manufactured but are still used in equipment such as r r r and r to name just a few to learn more about our refrigerant capabilities click the play now button to watch our video select the appropriate state for additional contact details in your area select your location alabama alaska arizona arkansas california colorado connecticut delaware district of columbia florida georgia hawaii idaho illinois indiana iowa kansas kentucky louisiana maine maryland massachusetts michigan minnesota mississippi missouri montana nebraska nevada new hampshire new jersey new mexico new york north carolina north dakota ohio oklahoma oregon pennsylvania puerto rico rhode island south carolina south dakota tennessee texas utah vermont virginia washington west virginia wisconsin wyoming one blue hill plaza pearl river ny   hudson technologies all rights reserved privacy policy  terms  conditions refrigerants refrigerants our products r information sf information industrial  compressed gases – dla sds  msds sheets refrigerant reclaim refrigerant reclaim clean exchange refrigerant buyback for wholesalers refrigerant buyback for large contractors  end users mixed refrigerant separation hydrostatic testing  cylinder maintenance environmental sustainability cfc disposal  carbon credits onsite refrigerant service onsite refrigerant services chiller decontamination chillers damaged by ruptured tubes high pressure chiller conversions refrigerant recovery sf sulfur hexafluoride recovery cross contaminated refrigerants refrigerant oil  analysis programs global en